[[Category:8th-century BC works]] [[Category:1946 archaeological discoveries]] [[Category:Multilingual texts]] [[Category:Phoenician inscriptions]] [[Category:Luwian inscriptions]] [[Category:Archaeological discoveries in Turkey]] [[Category:Ancient Cilicia]] [[Category:Stone objects]] [[Category:8th century BC]] [[Category:Kadirli District]]

In physics, the '''Lamb–Mössbauer factor''' (LMF, after [[Willis Lamb]] and [[Rudolf Mössbauer]]) or '''elastic incoherent structure factor''' (EISF) is the ratio of elastic to total incoherent [[neutron scattering]], or the ratio of recoil-free to total nuclear resonant absorption in [[Mössbauer spectroscopy]]. The corresponding factor for [[coherence (physics)|coherent]] neutron or [[X-ray scattering]] is the [[Debye–Waller factor]]; often, that term is used in a more generic way to include the incoherent case as well.
When first reporting on recoil-free resonance absorption, Mössbauer (1959)<ref name=Mossbauer1959> {{Citation |last1=Mössbauer |first1=R. L. |year=1958 |title=Kernresonanzabsorption von Gammastrahlung in Ir<sup>191</sup> |journal=[[Naturwissenschaften]] |volume=45 |issue=22 |pages=538–539 |doi=10.1007/BF00632050|bibcode = 1958NW.....45..538M |language=de}}</ref> cited relevant theoretical work by Lamb (1939).<ref name=Lamb1939> {{Citation | last1=Lamb |first1=W. E. | year=1939 | title=Capture of Neutrons by Atoms in a Crystal | journal=[[Physical Review]] | volume=55 |issue=2 |pages=190–197 | doi=10.1103/PhysRev.55.190|bibcode = 1939PhRv...55..190L }}</ref> The first use of the term "Mössbauer–Lamb factor" seems to be by Tzara (1961);<ref name=Tzara1961> {{Citation | last1=Tzara |first1=C. | year=1961 | title=Diffusion des photons sur les atomes et les noyaux dans les cristaux | journal=[[Journal de Physique et le Radium]] | volume=22 |issue=5 |pages=303–307 | doi=10.1051/jphysrad:01961002205030300 |language=fr|bibcode=1927JPhRa...8..225D }}</ref> from 1962 on, the form "Lamb–Mössbauer factor" came into widespread use.
Singwi and Sjölander (1960)<ref> {{Citation | last1=Singwi |first1=K. | last2=Sjölander |first2=A. | year=1960 | title=Resonance Absorption of Nuclear Gamma Rays and the Dynamics of Atomic Motions | journal=[[Physical Review]] | volume=120 |issue=4 |pages=1093 | doi=10.1103/PhysRev.120.1093|bibcode = 1960PhRv..120.1093S }}</ref> pointed out the close relation to incoherent neutron scattering. With the invention of [[neutron backscattering|backscattering spectrometers]],<ref> {{citation |last1=Alefeld |first1=B. |last2=Birr |first2=M. |last3=Heidemann |first3=A. |year=1969 |title=Ein neues hochauflösendes Neutronenkristallspektrometer und seine Anwendung |journal=[[Naturwissenschaften]] |volume=56 |issue=8 |pages=410 |doi=10.1007/BF00593617|bibcode = 1969NW.....56..410A |language=de}}</ref> it became possible to measure the Lamb–Mössbauer factor as a function of the [[wavenumber]] (whereas Mössbauer spectroscopy operates at a fixed wavenumber). Subsequently, the term ''elastic incoherent structure factor'' became more frequent.
