'''Musselroe Wind Farm''' is a [[wind farm]] at [[Cape Portland, Tasmania|Cape Portland]], [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]].<ref>Alan Copeland. ''[http://www.abareconomics.com/publications_html/energy/energy_09/EG09_Oct.pdf Electricity Generation Major Development Projects -- October 2009 Listing]'', [[ABARE]], November 2009, p. 9.</ref> It is third wind farm in the state, being owned and operated by [[Hydro Tasmania]]. It consists of 56 [[Vestas V90-3MW]] wind turbines, with a generating capacity of 168 MW. The energy output from the Musselroe Wind Farm will be sufficient to supply electricity to around 50,000 households and abate 450,000 tonnes of {{CO2}} emissions annually.<ref>Alison Andrews: [http://www.examiner.com.au/story/1175169/musselroe-wind-farm-to-light-up-tasmania-from-february/ "Musselroe wind farm to light up Tasmania from February "] in The Examiner, 10 December 2012</ref>

The first 37 turbines have been connected to the grid in 2013,<ref>Tim Walker and Leon Compton: [http://www.abc.net.au/local/audio/2013/04/23/3743684.htm "Musselroe Windfarm online"] on ABC, 23 April 2013</ref> and the full farm was completed in January 2014.<ref>Mounster, Bruce: [http://www.themercury.com.au/news/tasmania/energy-future-lies-in-the-wind-as-tasmania-is-urged-to-embrace-a-world-class-resource/story-fnj4f7k1-1226805037613 "Energy future lies in the wind as Tasmania is urged to embrace a 'world-class resource'"] in ''[[The Mercury (Hobart)|The Mercury]]'', 19 January 2014</ref>

