'''Stearidonic acid''' (SDA) is an [[Omega-3 fatty acid|ω-3 fatty acid]], sometimes called '''moroctic acid'''.  It is biosynthesized from [[alpha-linolenic acid]] by the enzyme [[delta-6-desaturase]].  Natural sources of this [[fatty acid]] are the seed oils of [[hemp]], [[blackcurrant]], [[Lithospermum arvense|corn gromwell]]<ref>http://www.niab.com/pages/id/319/Corn_Gromwell</ref> and [[Echium plantagineum|echium]] (although the plant is a source of stearidonic acid, it is toxic for human consumption), and the [[cyanobacteria|cyanobacterium]] [[Spirulina (genus)|''Spirulina'']].

