'''Zinc ricinoleate''' is the [[zinc]] [[salt (chemistry)|salt]] of [[ricinoleic acid]], a major [[fatty acid]] found in [[castor oil]]. It is used in many [[deodorant]]s as an odor-adsorbing agent. The mechanism of this activity is unclear.<ref>{{cite journal | last=Kuhn|first=H.|author2=F. Müller |author3=J. Peggau |author4=R. Zekorn |date=April 18, 2000|title=Mechanism of the odor-adsorption effect of zinc ricinoleate. A molecular dynamics computer simulation|journal=Journal of Surfactants and Detergents|volume=3|pages=335–343|publisher=Springer Berlin/Heidelberg|issn=1097-3958|doi=10.1007/s11743-000-0137-9|url=http://www.springerlink.com/content/q17655204020tw43/}}</ref>
